translated: Engström, Gunnar, public school inspector, Skara, born on March 26th, 1899 in Rydaholm, Jönköping county, the first child of public school teacher Karl Peter E. Engström and Emma Engström. Married to Märta Nykvist in 1928, they have two children: Gunnel, born in 1929, and Anders, born in 1932. Engström completed his education with a public school teacher's examination in 1920, a bachelor's degree in philosophy in 1928, and a licentiate degree in philosophy in 1935. He worked as a public school teacher in Kalmar from 1920 to 1922 and in Gothenburg from 1922, and as a public school inspector in Skara and its surrounding regions since 1942. He has authored several works including "Nordre Göta älv" (1934), "Sänkverket v. Bohus o. redutten på Fiskarholmen" (1935), "Industrin i Gbg m. förorter" (1937, co-authored with O. Jonsson), "Folkskolans läsebok: Geografi II" (1939, co-authored with G. Wilkke), and "Geografi III" (1947, co-authored with G. Wilkke and F. Äkes'son).
